      "message": "This should also explicitly state whether sub-checks should be individually re-runnable.  My recollection of our discussion at the hackathon is fuzzy -- I think it was suggested that the checker should include a flag for each sub-check indicating whether it is individually re-runnable, and if so, and the user clicks the re-run button for an individual sub-check, that we re-set both the sub-check and the overall check status to NOT_STARTED, notify the checker, and it should notice the change in sub-check status and know to re-run that sub-check.\n\n(We likely won\u0027t take advantage of this in Zuul in the forseeable future, as the immutability of buildsets (collections of jobs run on a change) is fairly well baked in at the moment, so we\u0027ll set that flag to false on all sub-checks.)",
